From 77bc4d4e7af845e7f373b285931dbbb27ad5a13d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 20:09:48 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add pre/post EQ, segmented shaper switch, and dark UI theme
 (milestone 3)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DSP:
- New dsp/filter.rs: biquad filter (Direct Form II Transposed) with peaking EQ
  and high-shelf modes. Coefficients recomputed once per buffer.
- Signal path is now: osc → pre-EQ peak → shaper → DC block → post-EQ shelf → amp.
- Pre-EQ boost into the saturator generates the rawstyle "screech"; high-shelf
  post-EQ tames harshness. Both default to 0 dB (acoustically transparent).
- New params: pre_eq_freq, pre_eq_q, pre_eq_gain, tone.

UI:
- Custom segmented switch (pill shape) for the shaper model replaces the slider.
  Active segment glows with accent colour + dot indicator; inactive segments dim.
- Global dark egui theme applied via set_style on init.
- New EQ section in the editor with Screech Hz / Q / dB and Tone controls.
- Section headers now use monospace font and accent colour for a cleaner look.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01GwURq9bT1AzMqUHKVyWkmv
